[13:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'instead of using traditional meshes, Trellis 2 uses what are called oxels. These are like selective 3D pixels. In a simple sense, they only exist where geometry is actually needed. So, it\'s'

[14:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'not like filling up any empty space. And then there\'s one voxil that handles geometry, such as the shape of the object, and then another one that handles the material or basically the appearance of the object, like the base'

[14:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'color or how metallic or reflective or how transparent it is. And merging both the shape and the material or basically the surface together allows it to create some super realistic and accurate objects. Now 3D model data is huge. So'

[14:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Trellis 2 also compresses this very efficiently using this sparse compression VAE. This basically shrinks the 3D data by like 16 times in each dimension. So a massive like 1024'

[14:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'resolution 3D object can be compressed down to only 9.6K tokens. Now if you scroll up to the top of the page, the awesome thing is they\'ve released a free hugging face space for you to try this'

